    "body": "### Problem\n\nBisect: 29a46a11aa0820e4efcad80a2dfb9ca600924f58 (@luukvbaal).\n\nFrom that commit `search_cmd` messages seem to be shown unconditionally.\n\n<img width=\"957\" height=\"320\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e6243913-15de-4f12-9e88-42ab3b3c9a5d\" />\n\nAlso the line similar to the status line is not very useful in this case and covers the current line. Maybe https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/38008 is related. \n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nIn the Nvim repo \n- `nvim --cmd \"lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable({msg = {target = 'msg'}})\" +se\\ cmdheight=0 README.md` \n- `/vim<CR>16n` \n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe pattern isn't shown ike in legacy UI:\n<img width=\"957\" height=\"320\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/e83358fb-be58-44e1-a9d9-fa3ce6dc252b\" />\nand the statusline is displayed correctly.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nfrom v0.12.0-dev-2340+g29a46a11aa  but v0.12.0-dev-2385+gf90cd620c5 too\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
